Articles.Content:
Hi, i recently installed KSP on my laptop and it was working fine for several days until i tried to play today. I had just tried to copy a save file from a different pc and play it on this one when i first encountered the problem. I started KSP and didnt notice the problem yet although i believe it may have already begun, but when i opened the save file it loaded, but started rapidly switching between a being normal and "not responding". I figured this was possibly because i had seperate mods installed on the other version and i quickly matched the mods on my laptop to my desktop pc's installation. After that i tried to open KSP again and immediately noticed the problem after the initial loading screen. Once at the menu the game will begin the rapid switching, but if i manage to click in between the freezes i can access the save file and see that it does load. Determined, i deleted all mods from the game and reloaded again, to no avail. At this point i decided a fresh install would be in order, so i deleted the game files and uninstalled the program. Reinstalling once more, i decided this had to work, as it was working perfectly the other day, WITH mods installed. Nope. Well i figured since the fresh install was not enough, it could possibly be a problem with steam. I haven't installed any other games on this laptop so i couldnt check by opening another game, so i just uninstalled steam as well and then reinstalled that, afterwards reinstalling KSP and it STILL doesn't work. Plz halp. Upon further investigation it seems to be happening specifically when i click. If i dont click for a while, the problem will kind of stop.

again to be clear, i am currently running a clean fresh install of the game, but have previously had mods installed (though any residual files should have been shredded by my uninstaller program)

KSP Version 1.0.5.1028 -steam version


Specs : Dell Latitude E5430

intel core i5-3230m @ 2.6ghz

8gb ram

250gb SSD

OS = 64bit Windows 8.1
